Package: basksim
Type: Package
Title: Simulation-Based Evaluation of Basket Trials 
Version: 0.1.0
AuthorsR: c(person("Sabrina", "Schmitt", "schmitt@imbi.uni-heidelberg.de", role = "aut"), 
            person("Lukas", "Baumann", "baumann@imbi.uni-heidelberg.de", role = "aut",
            comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-7931-7470"))
            )
Maintainer: Sabrina Schmitt <schmitt@imbi.uni-heidelberg.de>
Description: Provides a unified syntax for the simulation-based comparison of different single-stage basket trial
	designs with a binary endpoint and baskets of equal or unequal sample sizes. Methods include the designs by 
	Baumann et al. (2024) <doi:10.48550/arXiv.2309.06988>, Fujikawa et al. (2020) <doi:10.1002/bimj.201800404>,
	Berry et al. (2020) <doi:10.1177/1740774513497539>, Neuenschwander et al. (2016) <doi:10.1002/pst.1730> and	
	Psioda et al. (2021) <doi:10.1093/biostatistics/kxz014>. For the latter three designs, the functions are mostly 
	wrappers for functions provided by the packages 'bhmbasket' and 'bmabasket'. In addition, the package enables 
	the application of the design of Ollier et al. (2020) <doi:10.1177/0962280219886609> in the basket trial setting 
	and provides a new method that combines the two designs of Ollier et al. (2020) and Baumann et al. (2024).
